{"id": 243324600, "title": "Tanker driven by 15-year-old boy hits people in Pune\u2019s Kondhwa, 2 injured", "text": "At least two people were injured after a speeding tanker allegedly driven by a 15-year-old boy hit a two-wheeler and a few youngsters who were out exercising in Pune\u2019s Kondhwa on Saturday morning, the police said. The minor has been detained. The incident took place around 6.30 am in front of Everjoy Cooperative Housing Society near the National Institute of Bank Management (NIBM), Kondhwa. After receiving information about the accident, a team from Kondhwa police station rushed to the spot. The police identified the injured as Geeta Santosh Dhume (41) and Soni Chandrasingh Rathod. Dhume, a resident of Pisoli, was out for exercise with members of a sports academy in the Kondhwa area and was riding her two-wheeler when the accident took place, the police said. The injured have been admitted to a hospital in Kondhwa and are stable, the police added. Residents nabbed the tanker driver and handed him over to the police. The police have seized the tanker and are in the process of lodging a First Information Report (FIR), Santosh Sonawane, Police Inspector, said.", "summary": "", "url": "https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/pune/tanker-driven-by-15-year-old-boy-hits-people-in-punes-kondhwa-2-injured-9422113/", "image": "https://images.indianexpress.com/2024/06/WhatsApp-Image-2024-06-29-at-10.20.26-AM.jpeg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-29 04:57:17", "author": null, "language": "en", "source_country": "in", "sentiment": -0.27}